---
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Talks, Workshops & Away Days | WorkSmart-AI',
  description:
    'Focused AI sessions for conferences, team days and leadership away days in higher education. Keynotes, workshops and structured working sessions shaped around your audience.',
  canonical: '/services/talks-workshops/',
};

const sessionTypes = [
  {
    title: 'Keynotes and conference talks',
    description:
      'Sessions for HE conferences, sector events, all-staff days, and internal launches. Always tailored to the audience and the moment, so the room leaves with something they can act on rather than another general AI overview. Common themes include practical AI literacy for university staff, leadership clarity in an AI-shaped sector, and the honest boundaries between hype and useful adoption.',
  },
  {
    title: 'One-off workshops',
    description:
      'One hour, two hour, half-day or full-day sessions for a team, department, or cross-functional group. We start with what people actually do week-to-week and build the session around it, so by the end participants have tried things, made decisions, and have a clear sense of where to go next. Particularly effective for professional services teams, academic departments, and L&D groups.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Leadership away days',
    description:
      "Structured working sessions for senior teams who want to use the time well. Tailored to your institution's specific AI tools and policies, sessions are designed to produce something concrete by the end of the day: a shared view of where AI fits in your strategy, a sense of priorities, and the beginnings of a roadmap your team will actually own.",
  },
];
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <div class="bg-section px-6 pt-8 sm:px-8 lg:px-12">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
      <a
        href="/services/"
        class="inline-flex items-center text-sm font-semibold text-link transition-colors hover:text-accent"
      >
        ← Back to Services
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="bg-brand px-6 py-16 sm:px-8 lg:px-12 lg:py-20" data-aos="fade-up">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
      <p class="mb-4 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-secondary sm:text-sm">
        Talks, Workshops & Away Days
      </p>
      <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold leading-tight text-white sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl">
        Bring practical AI skills to your event, team, or leadership day
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-base leading-[var(--aw-leading-body,1.7)] text-white/90 sm:text-lg">
        Not every team needs a full programme. Sometimes what you need is a single focused session that helps people cut
        through the noise and leave with skills they can use.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-section px-6 py-16 sm:px-8 lg:px-12 lg:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-default bg-card p-6 shadow-card md:p-10" data-aos="fade-up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-heading sm:text-3xl">The idea behind this service</h2>
        <div class="mt-6 space-y-5 text-default">
          <p>
            Sometimes all a team needs to start is a single focused session: a conference keynote that helps an audience
            cut through the noise, a workshop that helps a team make sense of AI in their own work, or a leadership away
            day that turns scattered conversations into a shared direction. This service exists for exactly those
            moments.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl border border-default bg-card p-6 shadow-card md:p-10" data-aos="fade-up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-heading sm:text-3xl">Who it's for</h2>
        <div class="mt-6 space-y-5 text-default">
          <p>
            This works well for leadership teams who want to step back from the day-to-day and get properly aligned on
            AI; for departments and staff groups who want a hands-on session shaped around their own work; and for
            conference organisers and CPD leads who need a credible, sector-aware voice that speaks the language of
            higher education.
          </p>
          <p>If you have a budget for a one-off engagement and want it to actually land, this is where we start.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="mt-10 rounded-xl border-2 border-dashed border-primary/30 bg-card p-6 shadow-card md:mt-14 md:p-10"
        data-aos="fade-up"
      >
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-heading sm:text-3xl">How it usually takes shape</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-muted">Three formats, each shaped around your audience and what you want to achieve.</p>

        <div class="mt-8 space-y-6">
          {
            sessionTypes.map((session) => (
              <div class="rounded-xl border border-default bg-section p-5 md:p-7">
                <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-heading">{session.title}</h3>
                <p class="mt-3 text-default">{session.description}</p>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl border border-default bg-card p-6 shadow-card md:p-10" data-aos="fade-up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-heading sm:text-3xl">What makes these sessions different</h2>
        <div class="mt-6 space-y-5 text-default">
          <p>
            Our work sits inside higher education, not adjacent to it. The examples we use are drawn from real
            university work, the frameworks have been built and refined with HE clients, and the language is one your
            staff already speak: NSS, REF, exam boards, mitigating circumstances, external examiner workflows, and the
            rest.
          </p>
          <p>
            Just as importantly, we take a people-first view. Confidence and clarity matter more than the next shiny
            tool. Audiences leave feeling capable, not anxious.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl border border-default bg-card p-6 shadow-card md:p-10" data-aos="fade-up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-heading sm:text-3xl">What to expect</h2>
        <div class="mt-6 space-y-5 text-default">
          <p>
            Every booking starts with a short discovery call so we can understand your audience, your context, and what
            you want the session to achieve. From there we'll send a clear proposal covering format, content shape, and
            fee, and shape the session collaboratively in the weeks before it runs.
          </p>
          <p>We'll always agree what success looks like before we begin.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <section class="mt-10 rounded-2xl bg-brand px-6 py-12 text-center sm:px-10 md:mt-14 md:py-16" data-aos="fade-up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-white sm:text-3xl">
          Have an event, team day, or away day in mind?
        </h2>
        <p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-2xl text-white/90">
          The earlier the conversation, the better we can shape something that genuinely lands.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 sm:flex-row">
          <a
            href="/contact-us/"
            class="inline-flex min-w-[10rem] items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-accent px-8 py-3.5 font-semibold text-white transition-colors hover:bg-accent-hover"
          >
            Book a discovery call
          </a>
          <a
            href="/contact-us/"
            class="inline-flex min-w-[10rem] items-center justify-center rounded-full border-2 border-white px-8 py-3.5 font-semibold text-white transition-colors hover:bg-white/10"
          >
            Email us
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
